---
title: Prawn & Chorizo Orzo with Roasted Cheesy Tomatoes
description: A HelloFresh take on the crowd-pleasing classic, this paella-style recipe is made with velvety orzo pasta instead of rice. Bursting with rich earthy flavours, and requiring minimal prep and washing up, this one-pot wonder is about to become your weeknight go-to. Place this colourful dish in the middle of your table and enjoy in a traditional, communal style!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/prawn-chorizo-orzo-7ca07d6f-be4861ca.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/prawn-chorizo-orzo-5ada103130006c58636df112-ac0ad049.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/prawn-chorizo-orzo-5ada103130006c58636df112
author: Mimi Morley
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Spanish
nutrition:
  calories: 657 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 41 g
  sodium: 5.6 g
  serving size: 736
course: main course
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C and boil your #kettle{}. Remove the root and dark green top from the @leek{1}, halve lengthways, then slice into thin half moons. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200%g} through the equator. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways into 1cm strips, then chop into 1cm chunks. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{10%g} (stalks and all).

Pour the boiling @water{150%ml} into a #measuring jug{} with the @vegetable stock powder{1/2}, stirring until dissolved. Put the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} on a lined #baking tray{}, drizzle over a little @oil{}, sprinkle over a quarter of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Leave to the side for the moment.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the @chorizo{60%g}(diced) and cook until crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the leek and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes} more, then add the garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @orzo{180%g} and courgette to coat it in the chorizo-ey oil, then pour in the stock and diced tomatoes. Stir together.

At this point you can pop the tomatoes on the top shelf of your oven to roast until the cheese is slightly browned and the tomatoes are cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}. Bring the orzo to the boil, stirring constantly. Turn the heat to low and simmer away (don't let it boil rapidly) for ~{10-15%minutes}, stirring every couple of mins. After ~{5%minutes} of cooking, stir in the @king prawns{150%g}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque all the way through.

When the orzo is cooked and the liquid has been absorbed, remove from the heat and stir in the remaining hard Italian cheese.

> TIP: If all the liquid has been absorbed and the orzo is not quite cooked, just add 50ml of water and keep cooking, repeat this if you need to.

Taste the orzo mixture and add some salt and pepper if you feel it needs it, then stir in half the parsley. Spoon into #bowls{} and pop the tomatoes on top along with a sprinkling of remaining parsley. Enjoy!